                        <ns0:objectDesc>
                            <ns0:supportDesc>
                                <ns0:support>
                                    <ns0:p>Five connecting fragments of a white crystalline marble plaque, of which the right margin is damaged and the lower edge broken. Top, left and right edges are roughly finished. The rear is finished, but with a series of vertical grooves creating relief elements, with similarity to a triglyph. The marble has clearly been re-used from an earlier architectural element. The whole has been remounted on perspex.</ns0:p>
                                    <ns0:material ana="#material.stone.marble" ref="http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/48.html">marble</ns0:material>
